description: An IPA, Pleasant hop aroma with equally hop body taste…"A HOP HEADS HAPPY BEER"
name: Cannonball

description: Bold and Hoppy:  An American Style IPA with a citrusy hop bite and a subtle malt finish.
name: Cape Cod IPA

description: The brainchild of our taproom coordinator & Titanic fanatic, Ashley. This amber colored beer is brewed with Sorachi Ace hops to create subtle bitterness & a hoppy aroma. We’re sure that you’ll remember this IPA "every night in my dreams..."
name: Cape May Ashley’s Hops Will Go On

description: Winner of Best IPA at the 2012 Atlantic City Beer Festival! Intensely hoppy, very strong pale ale without the big maltiness; this beer is strongly hopped and clean, lacking harshness and a tribute to historical IPAs. The citrusy centennial hop was used generously as you can imagine.
name: Cape May Centennial IPA

description: A decidedly hoppy and bitter, moderately strong India Pale Ale (IPA). The beer emphasizes the hop aroma and flavor white muting the hop bitterness. Loaded with Cascade hops that provide Floral and citrus notes. It’s called India Pale Ale because it was a hoppier, more alcoholic version of the typical ale shipped to British troops in India in the 1800s. Turns out that hops and alcohol are a great preservative.
name: Cape May IPA

description: Brewed to be reminiscent of lazy days on the beach, here’s a super light ale, full of Cascade and Centennial hops (but no bitterness!). Go ahead, enjoy your day off - you deserve it.
name: Cape May Maggie’s Day Off IPA

description: Citrus peel, fresh cut grass and a hint of pine needles greet your senses as you approach this refreshingly balanced, dry-hopped American-style pale ale. This beer is dedicated to the hard work of the volunteers and supporters of the Virginia Capital Trail Foundation. Joining the historic and current capitals of Jamestown and Richmond, the Virginia Capital Trail will provide 50+ miles of cycling, running and walking paths through stunning cities, parks and wilderness in the heart of the Old Dominion. Your purchase of this beer supports the Virginia Capital Trail Foundation.
name: Capital Trail

description: Captain Molly Kool was North America’s first female licensed Atlantic sea captain. She was ahead of her time with strong ties to the Bangor area and Geaghan’s Pub. Like Molly, our newest IPA, Capt. Kool, is bold, brash and beautifully balanced. Jason’s blending and well timed additions of Cascade, Columbus, and Chinook hops have produced by far our biggest IPA with an ABV of 7.5% and 70 IBU and still a smooth easy drinking ale. Capt. Kool IPA is our tribute to the strong, brave women we all admire.
name: Capt. Kool IPA

description: Created after the hoppy ales brewed in the 1700’s for the long journey from England to Hawaii, this Ale is one of our hoppiest beers ever using 15 pounds of hops for 155 gallons of beer.
name: Captain Cook’s IPA

description: The Captain’s Pale Ale is a medium bodied American pale ale. We used four varieties of hops from the Pacific Northwest region to give this beer a strong, spicy bitterness with a smooth finish. Hints of grapefruit from the hops lend a little sweetness to the taste, which is also complimented by a grassy nose. This beer has quite a strong flavor at first, but once you start drinking it, it’s hard to stop.
name: Captain's Pale Ale

description: The Muddled Sweetness of roasted pineapple Is a gentle reminder that all fruit is not created equal. The hint of sweet tropical flavor brings out the best in this IPA
name: Caramelized Pineapple IPA (Ghost 260)

description:
The Carneros India Pale Ale showcases our estate grown hops and diverse 80 IBUs hop profile packed into a full-body, malty and well balanced cerveza. You will sense the rich floral piney bouquet while enjoying a full flavor mid-palate with hints of malty sweetness and overall balance.

Hand crafted with 100% 2-row pale malt with hints of caramel malts brewed in small batches using selected bittering hops and an abundance of estate grown Saaz and other noble hops.
name: Carneros IPA

description: Our IPA is more heavily hopped and higher in alcohol than our Pale Ale. It is brewed with pale, caramel and cara-pils malts and finished with lots of Cascade and Crystal hops for a strong, citrus/piney flavor and aroma. It is 5.4% alcohol.
name: Carolina India Pale

description: Ripe with aromas of mango and tropical fruits followed by layered flavors of bright hop bitterness, warm alcohol and sweet mango that becomes stronger as it warms in your glass.
name: Carpe Brewem Imperial Mango IPA

description: This heavily hopped, full-bodied IPA is cask conditioned and served via traditional hand-pulled beer engine. Naturally carbonated at cellar temperature to emphasize expansive grapefruit esters and malt character.
name: Cascade Canyon Cask IPA

description: Light in color, medium body, with a hop bitterness and Cascade hop finish.
name: Cascade I.P.A.

description: The third in the series of single hop IPA's from Mikkeller. Brewed with Cascade, a true american classic hop type. This hop is less powerfull than the ones used in the previous two single hop IPA's - creating a great balance with the beers other aspects.
name: Cascade Single Hop IPA

description: An experimental batch as we begin to work on our first ever IPA recepie! Our brewing apprentice Brad has been sufficiently mocked, loved and sweat while bringing the first batch to life!
name: Cascadian Dark Ale

description: Description
name: Cascading Black IPA

description: Light amber in color with berry, pink grapefruit, and lychee in the aroma. Called a "benchmark Northwest IPA" by the Tacoma Brews Tribune Blog. Heavily hopped, but well balanced. Hops include Amarillo, Centennial, and Simcoe. Rotating dry hop! Check with your bartender to find out what the most recent hops are. Currently, this is Columbus and Mosaic.
name: Cask Supergoose IPA

description:
Served in Cask
Schlafly Tasmanian IPA is brewed with 100% Australian hops. The Tasmanian hop, Galaxy, is a strong, aromatic variety that is different from traditional strains of the Pacific Northwest. Our brewers developed a recipe that showcases the hop’s unique flavors of citrus and pineapple.
name: Cask Tasmanian IPA

description: We've taken our IPA and amped it to dizzying heights with more malty goodness and Cascade hops.
name: Cassk Kickin’ IPA

description: This time of year, there is no more coveted hop than the Galaxy from Australia, which was originally populated by England's outcast convicts. Outcast IPA employs these hops generously from hop back to dry hopping stages. Yet the result is a balanced and bronzy ale, with medium hop bitterness complimented by moderate maltiness, showcasing aromas and flavors reminiscent of passion fruit. Released on the heels of Nothwest-hopped Insider IPA, Outcast is a secret handshake between hemispheres.
name: Cast Out

description: Crisp and citrusy, this India Pale Ale derives its atypical dark copper brown color from malted chocolate wheat.  Heavily hopped, the Chocolate Orange IPA’s bitterness blends with the dark chocolate flavors of the cocoa nibs added during fermentation.  Those subtle chocolate notes rest behind a floral bouquet, enhanced by additions of bitter orange peel and dry hopping with Citra.
name: Castaway Chocolate Orange IPA

description: A full-bodied, American-Style I.P.A. that is bronze in color, Castaway IPA is "dry hopped" (aged with liberal amounts of whole hop flowers after fermentation) for assertive hop flavor and aroma. The bitterness is balanced by the malty body of the beer.
name: Castaway IPA

description: An IPA intended for testing purposes with a calculated yeild well within the parameters of a standard India style pale ale. The tests indicated about three times the proposed yeild. This IPA blends three different types of hops wich come together on the tongue to form the most explosive IPA yet tasted. Despite our best efforts, it has been unleashed upon the public. Enjoy the fallout!
name: Castle Bravo

description:
This pungent IPA recipe was like a phoenix that rose from the ashes of hop politics. Faced with a serious shortage of Citra in early fall (2013), we had to put the production of Roman Candle momentarily on hold. In its absence, and to mend our broken hearts, we devised a recipe that was all about utilizing the pungent citrusy kick of two hops we call favourites here: Summit and Simcoe. The malt body is extremely light, which allows the focus to stay on the hops, both in aroma and bitterness.

The final product took us a bit by surprise: it wasn't just a runner up, but a hoppy sensation that would prove to give Roman serious competition. You decide which IPA reigns supreme.
name: Cat Lady IPA

description: You love all of your children, but you might love some just a little more. All of our brews are our babies and with this one there is a lot to love. Copious hops with a crisp finish; this IPA is built out of all the best things we loved from our favorite IPA’s combined into one brilliant result. Take a drink, take two and enjoy!
name: Cataclysm Imperial IPA

description:
For coastal locals like us, the annual hurricane season is equal parts fun and terror. We all follow a series of storms with weird names like other folks follow pro sports teams, tracking paths and occasionally buying bulk batteries and jugs of spring water. The least we could do is brew some beer to help alleviate anxiety during these tense months. The Hurricane Series of IPAs, with varying strengths corresponding to each of the storm categories, is a public service of HCB.

The ABV on Category 2 IPA, brewed on September 19, 2012 and the third in the series, makes it sound like a tame beast. The hop schedule, however, is a wild animal. Copious hopping in the boil with Simcoe, Citra, Ahtanum, and Cascade was followed up with a 10lb Amarillo dry-hop. The end result is an IPA with a citrusy aroma and arresting bitterness. If this doesn't take your mind off the stormy Atlantic, nothing will.
name: Category 2 IPA

description:
For coastal locals like us, the annual hurricane season is equal parts fun and terror. We all follow a series of storms with weird names like other folks follow pro sports teams, tracking paths and occasionally buying bulk batteries and jugs of spring water. The least we could do is brew some beer to help alleviate anxiety during these tense months. The Hurricane Series of IPAs, with varying strengths corresponding to each of the storm categories, is a public service of HCB.

Category 3, the first brewed in the series, was originally brewed on September 27th, 2011. It sits squarely in the middle of the IPA-ABV range, hence the category. Centennial hops dominate this one, used both in the boil and the dry-hop.
name: Category 3 IPA

description:
For coastal locals like us, the annual hurricane season is equal parts fun and terror. We all follow a series of storms with weird names like other folks follow pro sports teams, tracking paths and occasionally buying bulk batteries and jugs of spring water. The least we could do is brew some beer to help alleviate anxiety during these tense months. The Hurricane Series of IPAs, with varying strengths corresponding to each of the storm categories, is a public service of HCB.

The second member of the series, Category 4, was originally brewed on November 23, 2011, at the very tail-end of that year’s hurricane season. A minty hop profile provided highlights to this otherwise strong IPA.
name: Category 4 IPA

description: This is a beer that calls upon the deliciousness of two styles we love: IPAs and Belgian ales. Refreshing and flavourful, Catherine Wheel is an untraditional Belgian/American melange.
name: Catherine Wheel

description: A super pale, single malt (Best Malz Pilsner), single hop (Chinook) I.P.A. inspired by the effect of catnip on our brewery cat, Fuggle. If only beer could make us that happy… Catnip is our best shot - a light-colored, deceptively strong and hoppy beer with grapefruit and pine hop flavors and a refreshing tartness and ‘funk’ from our Belgian Wit yeast.
name: Catnip

description: A blend of old world traditions. Brewed like an IPA, it blends pine and citrus hop flavors with hints of pineapple and pear from a secret Belgian yeast strain.
name: CattyWompus

description: A slightly spicing, piney addition to the Glasstown IPA family. You will also get hints of grapefruit in the finish.  This is truly a wonderful IPA that mimics the color of our world renowned cedar swamps here in southern New Jersey.
name: Cedar Swamp IPA

description: A classic American-style IPA is good any time of the year, and thats why we are happy to bring you our Cellarman’s Reserve Single Hop IPA Series with year-round availability. In order to highlight the hops, the base of the beer is a simple recipe comprised only of 2-row and Munich malts. A 7% abv gives us just the right amount of balance for 65 IBUs of hoppy goodness coming from using only one single hop varietal for bittering, flavor, and dry-hopping additions. Next comes the Martin House twist. While its availability is year-round, the hops we use will not be. From time to time, whenever our Cellarmen feel like it, we’ll switch out that single hop. While the beer overall will remain the same, the drinker will get to experience the nuances of each hop varietal.
name: Cellarman's Reserve

description: There ís nothing traditional about this traditional Indian Pale Ale. Amber in color with an INTENSE maltiness perfectly balanced with a spicy hop flavor. Carefully dry hopped at the end of its fermentation cycle with Centennial Hops. The ALE that cures all that ALES you!!!
name: Centennial Ale

description: A classic Northwest IPA brewed with crystal malts that give it a rich golden color. Centennial hops provide a floral nose and sharp bitter finish.
name: Centennial India Pale Ale

description: This copper-colored ale is an extra-big beer! More malt. More hops. IPA was originally brewed big for the trip from Britain to India. First brewed here to celebrate our 100th brew, we now brew this one when we thirst for a big, big beer!
name: Centennial India Pale Ale

description: This India Pale Ale was made to celebrate the 100th anniversary of Glacier National Park.  Floral and citrusy hop profile.  Montana-grown 2-row pale, wheat, caramel, Vienna, and honey malts.  Centennial hops.
name: Centennial IPA

description: Get ready to bask in the glory of the frothy head’s floral bouquet. Relish the citrus accents from the abundance of dry hopping. This one’s sweet, yet balanced. Malty undertones shake hands with the hop character for a finish that never turns too bitter.
name: Centennial IPA

description: A well-balanced IPA with notes of citrus and big malt body.
name: Centennial Park

description: Flavorfully bitter.  A slight sweetness rounds out the finish.  Floral, fruity nose.  Made with ALL MICHIGAN HOPS!
name: Centennial Slam

description: A single hop IPA made with citrusy centennial hops and traditional English malt, which gives it a rich body and amber color with a slight citrus bite.
name: Centennial X’s 5

description:
“The harvest season is coming early, and so too are the cooler temperatures. Center Street Series #1 is created to make the most of the crisp air and let you enjoy every bit of the short autumn season. It is hand crafted with tradition in mind, but always with a little MB twist. 

The malt is the key to Center Street Series #1 with the hops taking a break. Much like its German inspired relatives, you see its brilliant amber color and smell its rich malt base. The flavor follows the aroma, and is toasty with a touch of sweetness and a slight noble hop presence. 

We all know that autumn goes way too fast in Minnesota. Take the time to sit down and enjoy both the season and Center Street Series #1. It won’t be long before neither one of them will be around.”
name: Center Street Series #1

description: Located in the heart of St. Petersburg, Central Oak is the only neighborhood in the city to cross Central Avenue. Many of the homes sit among beautiful brick streets and the neighborhood boasts a 1.5 acre park. Central Oak is our Green Bench IPA aged on American White Oak spirals that adds an oak-y complexity, and accentuates the dry, fruity flavors of the base beer.
name: Central Oak IPA

description: Session IPA brewed and flavored with Green Tea
name: Ceremony

description: An aggressively hopped IPA balanced with full flavored floor malted 2-row barley.
name: Ceremony IPA

description: This beer is a part of a Single Hop IPA series by Mikkeller. We created this series to showcase hop varieties on their own. This gives the consumer the possibility of smelling and tasting the unique characteristics of each variety and hopefully helping to educate people about the wonderful world of hops. For each beer, the single hop variety was used in the same weight for bittering, aroma and flavor and for dry hopping. All 19 varieties of single hop beers in this series were brewed the same week and with malts from the same batches and the same yeast and fermentation temperatures. This is done to better compare the characteristics of the different hop varieties.
name: Challenger Single Hop IPA

description: Champion Reserve I.P.A. – An American style IPA, mediun to light amber in color with a floral hoppy aroma. Meduim bodied and hopped to about  60 IBU's. It's brewed using British malts and generously hopped with a blend of Perle and Cascade.  It's dry-hopped with Cascade for a fuller aroma.  5%alc.
name: Champion Reserve I.P.A.

description: This IPA does not need a compass to point you in the right direction to return to the islands. The flavors of this Session IPA will getyou to sit, relax, and enjoy the beautiful islandsunset from any local spot. Channel Marker IPA pairs perfectly with cracked conch.
name: Channel Marker IPA

description: Charity Island IPA has a bold and assertive hoppy characteristic. Brewed with 100% malted barley, the five hop additions give an aroma with a rich citrus, floral, and resinous bouquet. The crisp flavor is in perfect harmony with the malt backbone with a refreshing, clean, and dry finish.
name: Charity Island India Pale Ale

description: Charter Oak's Wadsworth India Pale Ale beer (named after Captain Joseph Wadsworth, for it was he who actually rode off to hide the Charter in the Charter Oak Tree)  is our American style IPA with plenty of hop aroma and bitterness, yet crisp, refreshing and not over the top! Our Charter Oak IPA style will please your palate with more than your typical 'every day India Pale Ale' and you'll be sure to taste our grapefruit citrus overtone backed with notes of malted caramel. Our beer is a medium bodied beer with a rich amber shade. Plenty of choice, high Alpha hops that we hand select, yet well balanced and not too intense for the best locally brewed IPA from our specialty malted barley.
name: Charter Oak's Wadsworth IPA

description: A heavenly IPA that is packed full of fresh hops whose variety changes every year. This beer is perfect for those who like it bright, deep and fresh. There aren’t any groomers or gapers mucking it up around here – just unblemished flavor.
name: Chasin' Freshies

description: IPA featuring Galaxy hops.
name: Chazzwazzer

description: Tradisjonelle humletyper, og store mengder, gjør denne IPA-en til en klassiker. Den er brygget på cascade og anthanum som gir en smak av blomster og sitrus. Balansen mellom munich- og caramelmalt gir god kropp uten at ølet blir for søtt. Velkommen til 1996.
name: Check In IPA

description: Our original IPA has a rich, balanced malt profile and features the floral aroma of Cascade hops.
name: Chehalem Mountain IPA

description: Born from an idea at the 2014 Hopsauce Festival, a fantastic Hop Sauce Love child in a collaboration with The Chicken or the Egg. One might ask if there were not wings, would there be beer? And if there were not beer, would there be wings? Thus the Chicken or the Egg IPA hatched. With stinging undertones, a kiss of honey we are proud to threaten you with this new epicurean mashup.
name: Chicken or the Egg

description: Chickity China The Chinese Chicken is our wet-hopped IPA brewed with fresh Citra and Mosaic hops from the Pacific Northwest. This beer is dripping with dank juicy hop goodness, but remains balanced by a firm malt backbone that's enhanced by a hefty addition of malted oats. This one-of-a-kind, once-a-year brew offers notes of guava, mango, honeydew melon and lemon, with a full-bodied mouthfeel and a long, explosive hoppy finish.
name: Chickity China The Chinese Chicken

description: From shrubland to woodland to highland, you’ve creekcrossed and switchbacked through it all today. You pause on the trail for a moment and crack open a Chief Peak. The piney hops are first to arrive. The tropical tones of passion fruit, orange, and gooseberry aren’t far behind. Watch as the sky blends from orange to blue. Look out on the valley and trace the contours of the mountain. Breathe in the thinning air, wipe the sweat from your brow, and take another well-earned sip.
name: Chief Peak

description: The original India Pale Ales were brewed for export with lots of hops and high gravity to help them survive long journeys by sea. Chilkoot Trail follows suit using Amarillo and Cascade hops for a floral and citrus flavor. An assertive bitterness and soft alcohol warmth are supported by a strong malty backbone.
name: Chilkoot Trail IPA

description: Black IPA
name: Chinook

description: The Chinook IPA is brewed with a single hop variety. The Chinook hop gives this IPA a nice floral aroma and the addition of caramel malts adds a hint of sweetness.
name: Chinook IPA

description: Brewed to style, this India Pale Ale highlights the unique characteristics of the Chinook hop.  Spicy, piney, grapefruity aromas and flavors are complemented and balanced by a complex sweetness added by the crystal malt in the grain bill.  This beer's IBU level only reaches into the mid 40's which allows the spicy character of the Chinook hop to come through smoothly without a cloying hop bitterness.
name: Chinook IPA

description: Single hopped IPA with a massive amount of Chinook hops, Deep golden base with a long lasting citrus hop finish
name: Chinook IPA

description: A medium hopped ale with overtones of citrus from local Chinook hops for bitterness with a nice floral finish from Cascade hops.  A refreshing way to end a busy day.
name: Chinook IPA

description: Single-hop series featuring Chinook hops. Rye-infused IPA.
name: Chinook Single Hop IPA

description: Our award-winning IPA recipe is chockfull of Chinook hops and bursting with pine and citrus aromas and flavors. Careful, more than one of these will getcha schnocker'd!
name: Chinooker'd IPA

description: We hit this full bodied IPA with “nookie” four times during the brewing process to give this ale its trademark Chinook hop character. We then “dry nookied” this flavorful ale to further enhance its grapefruit and pine aroma.
name: Chinookie

description: One of our new IPAs, the Chnook is brewed with Chinook hops, giving this IPA a spicy and clean bitterness.
name: Chnook IPA

description:
This IPA is our choice here at Butchers Brewing. It is balanced with crisp pale malts and huge late additions of Amarillo hops. This beer’s hop profile is offset with sweet hints of caramel and biscuit flavors. The culinary craftsmanship that is the backbone of Butcher’s Brewing is embodied in this delicious IPA. Make it your choice, you won’t be disappointed.

This beer is bottle conditioned to be a natural live brew. This bottle has live yeast performing a slow secondary fermentation in it right now. Hold it up to the light, that sediment you see is proof. Swirl the bottle and drink it hazy or decant off the lees.

Support your local everything!
name: Choice Red IPA

description: Its medium body, amber color, bold flavor, and aroma will put in front of the drinker the definition of a fierce IPA. The backbone of this beer is the intense hop flavor combined with malty bitterness and a crisp floral finish. The mightiness of hops will attack your taste buds, and give them a pleasant and yet wild satisfaction.
name: Chupacabra

description: This is a full flavored IPA with a pronounced hoppy finish that is created by adding Amarillo hops at the end of fermentation. This ale, the only ale in our lineup at the present time, will withstand the long voyage to your local bar or refrigerator. With an alcohol by volume of 7.5%, as our friend Polo would say, "Asusta me one time!" (Scare me one time)
name: Chupahopra

description:
Our famous Inline IPA infused with fresh cilantro and lemon peels/zest.
Hoppy and refreshing.
name: Cilantro Lemon IPA

description: This beer sets the bar with its eye catching unfiltered hazy hue and amazing head that last. It’s euphoric aroma, great taste and smooth yet bold hoppy finish will absolutely stun not only your palate but your mind. Be prepared to be amazed!!
name: Circus City IPA

description: This is a very hop forward American style IPA. Brewed with Pale, Vienna, Munich and wheat malt for a solid base for all American hops, focusing mainly on the variety “Citra.” Citra hops are a relatively new variety introduced in 2008. It was bred as a hybrid of a number of different hops, including Hallertauer Mittelfrüh, U.S. Tettnanger, East Kent Golding, Bavarian, Brewers Gold, and other unknown hops. The resulting hop, Citra, has a distinct citrusy and tropical fruit flavor and aroma. In Citra ass down we used American Columbus for bittering and 11# of Citra at the end of the boil for late kettle addition flavor and aroma. Then we added 6 more pounds Citra and 5# Centennial post fermention for aroma. Rebrewed for your tasting pleasure!
name: Citra Ass Down

description:
HybriCitra Cyclus Belgian Style IPA

-Based on our Half Cycle IPA, this is a Belgian-style India Pale Ale.

-Same huge hop presence as Half Cycle, but with a slightly fruity, drier finish than its American cousin.
name: Citra Cyclus BS IPA

description:
As the name suggests, Citra Fresh IPA is made to be consumed
immediately. Hopped generously with the most sought after hop on planet Earth – Citra. Citra hops impart a smooth citrus
aroma and flavor in beer. We designed a delicate and soft malt
backbone to accentuate the hop flavor and added nearly a pound and a half of Citra hops per barrel, all added near the end of the boil, to get the most flavor and aroma from the hop. It’s a very freshy beer!
name: Citra Fresh

description: This recipe, designed by local Colorado home brewer Ryan Lotter was brewed on July 20th in collaboration between our head brewer Jeff Griffith and selected home brewer Ryan Lotter. It's a single hop IPA brewed with Citra hops.
name: Citra IPA

description: All the big hop flavor and aroma you’d expect from an IPA, showcasing mango and passion fruit flavors and aroma from Citra hops.  Finally, this IPA is made so that the bittering won’t linger too long, so you can enjoy that next sip – just right, an IPA that’s hoppy, but balanced at the finish.
name: Citra IPA

description: Brewed exclusively with Citra hops and 2-row malt. This IPA is bright and citrusy with tropical fruit notes of grapefruit , lychee and melon, finishing dry with a slight crisp grass note.
name: Citra S.M.A.S.H. IPA

description: Our Citra Session™ IPA is brewed with high-quality Marris Otter and Vienna malt but the flavor is dominated by the Citra hops introduced throughout the boil and again in the dry hop for maximum aroma intensity. Notes of lemon, orange and grapefruit make this hop-laden brew a perfectly potable summer session IPA.
name: Citra Session

description: An incredibly smooth and refreshing IPA using only Citra hops to balance the bitterness with citrus and tropical tones.
name: Citradelic Single Hop IPA

description: Citra hops and tangerine elevate each sip onto a plane of juicy, tropical pleasure. Expand your palate with a Citradelic experience.
name: Citradelic Tangerine IPA

description: An American-style IPA brewed and dry hopped with Citra hops to impart an intensely fruit, citrusy flavor and aroma.
name: Citramax

description: All citra hop IPA with lemon peel
name: Citraphilia

description: The luscious aromas and flavors of mango, grapefruit, orange, and melon make this juicy IPA one that begs you to enjoy more than one.
name: CitraSqueeze IPA

description: Citrocity is an IPA made in the Pacific Northwest tradition with hops that impart a distinctly grapefruit aroma and flavor. However, we’ve added Citra hops to this one, which give the beer hints of mango, papaya, and passion fruit. It’s nicely bitter and balanced by a strong malt backbone. Citrocity is the recipient of several awards throughout the Carolinas.
name: Citrocity

description: Handbuilt with fresh lemon zest and juniper
name: Citrum IPA

description:
In this day and age, there are seemingly infinite varieties of flavor compounds and aromatic properties available in the different breeds of hops that exist. Among them all, there is an undeniable “profile” that sticks out as most desirable by American IPA drinkers; that of the Citrusy hops of Washington and Oregon.

“Citrus” is certainly not our only IPA... but it was our first, and we wanted to make a statement. We at Funk Brewing Company believe in balance, complexity, and artistic brewing instead of “extreme beers”. That’s why we sought out to synthesize a beer that was masterfully crafted to accentuate a massive American Citrus hop profile while retaining our standards for balance, and sophistication.

Through various test batches, water profile manipulation, and uncommon hopping techniques, we found a way to offer you what we feel is the epitome of the American Citrus hop in a glass.
The utilization of Citra, Simcoe, Mosaic, and an experimental hop we like to call “LemonBomb”, give “Citrus” huge flavors and aromas of grapefruit, blood orange, pine, passionfruit, mango, and pink guava, balanced by a clean malt bill of Belgium’s finest pilsner malt and our neutral American yeast.

This will forever and always be our go-to IPA and we hope it becomes yours as well.
name: Citrus

description: Bold orange peel and honey aromas with a faint hint of bready malt define this IPA. The citrus and piney are both on full display, with tangerine and grapefruit notes that lead to a crisp spicy finish.
name: Citrus & Piney

description: Hand grated lemon zest is augmented by a hop combination that neatly walks the tightrope between sharp and sweet. The citrus core has additional notes or sherbet, lime and gentle spice.
name: Citrus and Sevens

description: This IPA has just what you need to get you ready for spring.  It is brewed with with CITRUSY hops: Columbus, Amarillo, Pilgrim, LEMON and ORANGE peel.  Then dry-hopped with more Amarillo for added HOPPY citrus punch.  The aroma is sweet yet the taste is dry with a great ROBUST IPA finish.
name: Citrus IPA

description: City of the Sun is a big, fruity, pungent, sticky, delicious IPA. Mosaic & Motueka give it a very fruity hop character, with Simcoe providing enough of a piney backbone to prevent it from going off the deep end. The complex but unobtrusive malt character gives it a medium body and a platform for the saturated hop flavor.
name: City of the Sun

description: A classic American IPA made with classic American ingredients. A blend of Columbus, Nugget and Galena provide a firm, bitter base that bears the full load of piney, grassy notes and deep hop flavors you expect from an IPA. The rocky, white head helps loft all those wonderful aromas right up to your snooter – so drink up!
name: Claim Jumper IPA

description:
A rich, fully-hopped India Paled Ale brewed for the true hop head. Light Copper in color. 

Malts: 2 Row Pale Malt, Carapils Malt, Caramel 20 Malt, Caramel 60 Malt, Hops: Cascade, Centennial, Fuggles.
name: Class Five IPA

description: Our India Pale Ale is a classic American beer.  A brilliantly clear, light copper color denotes the specialized caramel used to give the beer a light toasted malt flavor.  Classic NW American hops in both the boil & in ‘dry hopping’ are used to balance the malty sweetness of the barley and to give a wonderful herbal aroma.  Not too strong and not too bitter but a balanced, clean, dry, finished beer you will want to share with your friends.
name: Classic IPA

description: A straight forward citrus IPA.  Cliff Jumper is sure to please the most persistent hop head and yet this beer is still loved by all! Named for the days spent jumping from the rock bluffs at Rough River lake,  all it takes is one hop!
name: Cliff Jumper IPA

description: A prominent citrusy intense hop aroma and bitterness dominates this style with some slight malty sweetness. Belma hops give pleasant fruity and floral characteristics that, along with Citra, Centennial and Cascade, imparts citrus flavors, tangerine, mango, grapefruit and pineapple. Late additions in the boil and during the whirlpool process and post fermentation for this beer provides intense hop aroma that is sure to please hop lovers.
name: Cloud 9

description: Brewed with 7 hop varietals: Amarillo, Cascade, Centennial, Citra, Galaxy, Nugget, and Summer. The Citra, Galaxy, and Amarillo dry hop gives it an immense citrus aroma and at 78 IBUsit has a big hoppy bite up front, but finishes as refreshing and clean as the calm after the storm.
name: Cloud Ripper

description: We know the idea of a "New England IPA" style is still in debate, but we still feel it's the best way to describe this extremely dry hopped, minimal bitter addition IPA brewed with significant protein contribution from wheat and oats.
name: Cloud Surfer

description: This unfiltered beer is a perfect dream. It's brewed with wheat and oats for a silky smooth body, and it finishes with a burst of citrusy hop flavor. You'll notice a nice blend of traditional Belgian brewing spices, including orange peel and coriander. It's hoppy and it's big, but it's very refreshing . In our opinion, it's really good, all the time, anytime.
name: Clouded Dream - High Peaks Collection

description: West coast style IPA.  A showcase of citrus hop character from start to finish.  Medium bodied with a dry finish.
name: Clovis Point IPA

description:
Single-Hop IPA 
Cluster hops were the dominant hop variety in the US brewing industry literally for centuries, and the forerunner of many of our modern Northwest varieties. They have a unique aroma with quite a bit of citrus and a heft of herbal goodness. The Clusterf#ck recipe features Clusters in the kettle, in the hop back, and especially in the fermenter for dry-hopping. Pilsner and honey malts form the baseline; Clusters make the melody.
name: Cluster

description: Pale ale’s not enough?  Jump into our India Pale Ale, which has more malt, more hops, more of everything.  Named for two of the oldest and classic English and American hops, our IPA brings this historic beer style into the 21st century.
name: Cluster Fuggle IPA

description: A classic English-style India Pale Ale, Coast to Coast weighs in at 7% alcohol by volume.  We brewd this beer with malted barley from California farmers, and use Columbus hops for a citrusy aroma and brisk bitterness.
name: Coast to Coast IPA

description: This American Style IPA, is focused on a hop flavor aroma and bitterness. The three different hop varieties in the boil consisting of warrior, zythos, and chinook bring out a piney, bitter, resinous flavor.  Post fermentation the addition of Cascade and Nugget Dry hops introduces  a grapefruit aroma.  The abundance of Malt comprised of  Pale, Crystal, and a touch of White Wheat balances out this beer, giving it Dank flavor both Coasts can agree on.
name: Coast to Coast IPA

description: This IPA is third in the Coastal Series and full of American hops. It was dry hopped with Citra and Amarillo (think citrus and tropical fruit).
name: Coastal Series #3 IPA

description: Brewed with locally roasted Orinoco Ethiopian Yirgacheffe Coffee, Centennial and Azacca hops, this Brown IPA displays a hazy brown color with an off-white head. Aromas of citrus fruit, floral hops and coffee come through on the nose. The flavor profile comes through lightly roasted, with some subtle tropical fruit notes and a firm hoppy backbone.
name: Coffee Brown IPA

description: White IPA with coffee
name: Coffee Desirous

description: India Pale Ale infused with ozo coffee Ethopian Blend.
name: Coffee IPA

description: Born out of a mistake this beer made itself. A calculation mistake during a test batch doubled the intended hops in the brew. When we realized what we had done halfway through the brew we did the only thing we could do… we kept adding hops! The final product blew our expectations away so we decided to put it into production.
name: Cogway IPA

description: Stumptown Coffee Roasters’ Cold Brew Coffee is blended with an IPA made using Rogue Farms hops for a unique interplay of hops and coffee flavors. Opening with a huge hit of rich coffee aroma that is balanced by a not-so-subtle hop punch, the transition is seamless from one bold flavor to the next.
name: Cold Brew IPA

description: Colab ale is a beer that Dylan, the head brewer from Civil Life Brewing in Saint Louis, and I got together on and brewed here at my place with a new hop blend called Falconer's Flight. It's a 6.5% hoppy treat that has to be tried to believe.
name: Collaboration Ale

description:
Combining Boulevard’s expertise at making Belgian-style witbiers with Deschutes’ skill at brewing hop-forward ales, this beer puts a new spin on the idea of collaborative brewing. Working from a single recipe, brewmasters Steven Pauwels of Boulevard and Larry Sidor of Deschutes have produced two separate beers, more than 1,600 miles apart.

Despite the beer’s shared recipe, each of the two versions possess a unique identity, reflected in their naming and packaging. Boulevard’s half of the equation, christened Collaboration #2, is available throughout our selling region in both 750mL bottles and in kegs. Brewed at their Bend, Oregon facility, Deschutes’ effort is the second beer in their new Conflux collaboration series, and is available throughout their selling region in kegs and 22-ounce bottles.
name: Collaboration No. 2 - White IPA

description: In honor of this tradition of beer, not originally from USA, we called our IPA the Bastard. Then, because all of the Mu Board is from Colorado EXCEPT our internal “hop head”,  Mr Franklin, we rounded out the name in his honor, the Colorado Bastard. Using a blend of citrusy hops that add to the earthy flavor of the oak, our IPA can come across skunkier than a West Coast IPA.
name: Colorado Bastard IPA

description: An Imperial Pale Ale.  Think of this one as Slab Town's big brother.  Much bigger brother.  So big we can only allow 6 ounce tasters of this one.  11% ABV will do that to a beer.  Nice malt backbone, just enough sweetness to balance the hoppiness.  Limited quantities of this one to start with.  This is a test batch that we are happy with, we hope you are too!
name: Comatose

description: What’s this? A British-style IPA named after the man who defeated His Majesty’s Royal Navy in the War of 1812? Consider this a bold, hoppy (and mildly ironic) plunder of war.
name: Commodore Perry

description:
A medium-bodied and well hopped India Pale Ale with a dry, fruity aftertaste.

Name Origin: Like the naval officer and War of 1812 hero who battled the British enemy on Lake Erie, this brew is both distinctive and highly decorated.
name: Commodore Perry with Grapefruit Peel

description: This is an ale with zip. Our india pale ale brings together copious amounts of Columbus, Chinook and Cascade hops in a tasty combination that lingers through the finish and beyond. Compass delivers big hop flavor with malt in a nice supporting role. A hands-down favorite with the regulars in our Tasting Room.
name: Compass IPA

description:
The Nautical Compass Rose has helped Mariners find their way for centuries. Our Compass Rose IPA honors those who have dedicated themselves to building the proud tradition of our navy.

A refreshing IPA that launches with intense aromatic notes of sweet grapefruit and pear, balanced by a fresh grain breadiness and finishing with tropical notes of passion fruit and orange peel.
name: Compass Rose IPA

description: At first sip you’ll find this brew very similar to a typical West Coast IPA, but that quickly changes with giant notes of Rye and Chocolate accented by subtle citrus undertones. The final flavor experience is very similar to a strongly spiced Pumpernickel bread
name: Concrete Dinosaur

description: Our single hop wheat IPA, brewed with all Citra hops. Lighter in color and lower in a.b.v. than a typical American IPA, this beer has just the right amount of hop flavor and aroma. Completely satisfyingly awesome in its crispiness and well-rounded hopaliciousness. This beer might just be your Rushmore.
name: Conehead

description: American-style IPA that showcases Summit, Cascade, and Amarillo hops; a hop lovers dream. The use of these types of hops lends our IPA well balanced citrus, piney, floral, and somewhat spicy flavor and aroma. We only use the best pale and caramel malts to give this beer a smooth mellow mouth feel and a slightly sweet malt finish.
name: Confessional

description: Brewed to commemorate the amazing first flight that took place on a sand dune one mile from here.   Abundantly hopped with Galena, Amarillo, Simcoe, Willamette and Centennials; it’s one hoppy brew, (not for the faint of heart), neither is flight.
name: Conquest IPA

description:
Attention: You have just been conscripted into the 1st Roth Brewing Company.  The war against big beer is not over and you must fight!  You have been issued one 22oz Bomber.  It contains 92 IBUs with an OG of 1.042 SGU.  Fight well and one day you might go to beer valhalla. 

Hoppiness does not equal high gravity.
name: Conscription

description:
Loaded with hops like an IPA, yet drinks like a Pale Ale, we simply decided to call it a Strong Pale Ale. The fragrant, earthy citrus laced nose is instantly detectable. Large amounts of toasted grains and high alpha Simcoe hops form a perfect union that creates the cool sensation of toasted sourdough covered with zesty grapefruit hop marmalade.

Made exclusively for the City Park Grill.

ControversiALE was one of Shorts first beers and was made and named for the City Park Grill in Petoskey. Here is an excerpt from the Petoskey news explaining why Frank is Hangin:

It is said that the ghost of Frank Fochtman, former owner of the City Park Grill in Petoskey, haunts the establishment today. Manager Jason Septic said it is rumored that Fochtman hung himself in the basement, when it was named Grill Cafe. ”I know many people who’ve just had a weird sensation or feeling that there’s someone else down there,” he said, adding that his hair has stood up on the back of his neck on occasion when down in the basement.

The ghost has on occasion been blamed for broken glasses, when they would just snap as they sat on the table. ”They seemed to, when just sitting on the table, break where the stem meets the glass,” Septic recalled. However, despite some broken stemware, Fochtman — commonly just called Frank by the staff — does not seem to have a mean or negative presence. ”My personal feeling is that he’d be here, just watching over the place,” Septic said.
name: ControversiALE

description: Conundrum is a white wheat malt based IPA. We used Mosaic hops through out the brew for this hop. Triple hopped and dry hopped with Mosaic. The combination of American Wheat yeast and the mosaic hops creates a wonderful grapefruit aroma and taste. This cloudy beer (from the yeast) will have you thinking there must be grapfruit juice added to this beer, but there isn't....its quite the mystery, or conundrum.
name: Conundrum

description: A medium-bodied West Coast IPA. This one is all about the Pacific Northwest hops. This style starts you off with a big nose of citrus and takes you through a citrus hop bomb on the front of the palate with a dry finish carrying a hint of pine.
name: Cooper’s Parachute

description: A classic Northwest hoppy IPA done Amnesia style. Chinook hops bitter this beer (but not overly like many an IPA) while copious amounts of Amarillo hops take on the aroma both in the kettle as a finishing hop and in the fermenter as a dry hop.  Hugh notes of grapefruit and orange zest with a back bone of malt to carry out the finish.
name: Copacetic IPA

description:
This classic unfiltered IPA has a nice balance of hops and malt. Dry hopped with centennial hops and French oak for a delicate floral finish and subtle vanilla flavors. This is not a West Coast style hop-bomb.

On July 12, 1875 Henry Corbin’s Saloon, which was located just behind where Temperance Row Brewing Company is now located, was bombed by the local townspeople opposed to such an establishment in their town. Corbin rebuilt two years later and his new saloon suffered the same fate. We named our IPA in Henry’s honor.  Revenge is a beer best served cold.
name: Corbin's Revenge IPA

description: Corne du diable (French for "Horn of the devil") is a contemporary interpretation of the classic English India Pale Ale. This new style, born on the west coast of North America, is characterized by stronger and hoppier beers. The result is a red ale expressing caramel flavours coming from the malt, sharp bitterness and powerful hop aromas, thanks to dry hopping
name: Corne du diable

description: This unfiltered amber ale is packed full of hop bitterness, flavor and aroma. IPA is the most bitter beer style and it is enjoyed by people we refer to as “hopheads.” We dry hop this beer with a combination of English and American hop varieties for a wonderfully aromatic finish.
name: Cornerstone IPA

description: Red Wheat India Pale Ale
name: Cosmic Farmer

description: This west-coast style IPA boasts a unique fresh hop character that comes from the use of Australian Galaxy hops.
name: Cosmic IPA

description: This brew is a favorite for those who love hops! This medium copper-colored ale is dry hopped for a strong hop nose with medium malt overtones and hint of caramel that blend for one great tasting beer!
name: Cottonwood Endo India Pale Ale

description: Named after the coulter big cone pine tree this is a well-balanced I.P.A. It brings the beer style back to its roots. Brewed with a hit of rye for head retention and a deeper malt character, this beer has the best of all worlds, great hop aroma, a strong body and deceiving strength.
name: Coulter IPA

description:
The Vault Series is an extremely rare collection of limited release specialty craft beers that are high ABV of 9% or more and are aged a minimum of 6 to 8 weeks. 

Count Hopula is a bigger, bolder IPA brewed with Simcoe hops and huge amounts of caramel malt and roasted malts that give Count Hopula it’s blood red color.
name: Count Hopula Blood Red IPA

description: Mango, passion fruit, citrus, very hoppy.
name: Counter Strike

description: Dry, clean, crisp, and very citrusy. This beer is made for hop lovers. Centennial, Amarillo, and Cluster hops provide a wonderful hop aroma and flavor in this beer. Golden in color with grapefruit and lemongrass notes in the finish.
name: Country Boy IPA

description: This beer is Country Strong! An American IPA with a Country Strong citrus taste.
name: Country Strong

description:
Aromatic with a highly fruity and floral aroma. Subtle malt sweetness balanced by the hop aroma and bitterness.
An IPA with a blend of five different hops, four of them fresh and grown locally in Prince Edward County. Hops added 5 times during the brewing process to make it bitter and super hoppy.
name: County IPA

description: Our search for a location to start this brewery took us across much of Lower Bucks County, many times traveling down the well known divider between northern Philadelphia, southern Bucks, and Montgomery Counties….County Line Road.  One of the original names we thought of for the brewery was that of County Line Brewing Company.  I don’t know how or why we didn’t settle on that, but in recognition of our location so close to Philadelphia and that potential namesake, we decided to pass the name on to our flagship IPA that comes in at 6.63% ABV and is chock full of Warrior, Chinook, Simcoe, and Zythos hops.  It’s got a bready, slightly cracker-like malt backbone to counter some of that hop bitterness, but not so much that this four hop combination won’t put a smile on your face (or a giant pucker).  It’s got a huge citrus-grapefruit note with a nice lingering hop bitterness showing a complexity that few hugely hop forward IPAs lack.
name: County Line IPA

description: Michigan and west coast hops collide to form a fruit forward, smooth IPA. Tangerine and tropical fruits notes burst on the nose and have a subtle bitterness to compliment the finish.
name: Covariance

description: Cover Crop is a classic American IPA that delivers. It pours a deep brilliant copper with a bright white head. The initial flavor is a medium-bodied intense malt backbone that quickly reveals the spicy notes provided by the Rye, one of the worlds most widely-used cover crops. To balance such malt, citrusy hops assertively round out the flavor with a smooth bitterness. Cover Crop is a highly complex, yet very drinkable beer that's a perfect bridge between seasons. Spring Seasonal (March-May)
name: Cover Crop Rye IPA

description: Covert h'Ops dry hopped on Cascade.
name: Covert on Cascade

description: Covert h'Hops Black IPA dry hopped on Mosaic.
name: Covert on Mosaic

description:
Introducing Cow Puncher* India Pale Ale, a dry hopped west coast style IPA with a bold rugged flavor.

*3 Beards Beer Company does not support or encourage the punching of livestock. No cows were harmed during the production of this ale. Unless you count the pile of hamburgers consumed while developing this recipe.
name: Cow Puncher

description: A northwest IPA brewed with organic malts and organic Citra and Simcoe hops grown in the Cowiche Canyon of the Yakima Valley. We make Hop Lab in partership with Carpenter Ranches and the Britt family in an effort to expand the organic hop industry in Washington State. A portion of all sales fund the Cowiche Canyon Conservancy.
name: Cowiche Canyon Organic Hop Lab #1

description: A very nice American India Pale Ale that went through numerous trials to get it just right. This beer has a nice malt background for the hops that add a pine, citrus, and earthy flavors and aromas produced from the northwestern hops we use.
name: Coyote Morning IPA

description:
You remember the year you put that old Ford back together? Piece by piece you worked on that vintage machine, long into the nights, while Marty and Joe called the game on the radio and you cussing with every busted knuckle. Then, with that first crank, she fired up like she rolled right off the line and pride rushed through you like hi-test gasoline. And no, you can’t have that year back, but you can have a can of Crankshaft IPA, and the familiar beauty of those long-past days will return. Life is not about the destination, but the journey

A more approachable version of the typical American IPA, Crank Shaft has hop flavor and is aroma forward. Notes of citrus, mangoes, and tropical fruit dominate. The bitterness is more rounded than most, due to primarily late hop additions, as well as dry hopping. The use of three different types of malts give this brew a more balanced body and slight amber/light Caramel color.
name: Crank Shaft

description: A very balanced, complex, yet easy drinking IPA.  This beer has a multiple malt backbone that we balance with generous El Dorado hops among others. The flavor begins with big maltiness balanced with the bold aroma and bitterness from the El Dorado hops. Aromas of mango, orange, and pineapple balance with the malt and a crisp bitter finish.  A ruby orange color, 7% ABV, light amber head, and 70 IBUs.
name: Crank Yanker IPA

description: Love your hops? Then have a go at a Cranky! Our orange IPA is crammed full of US Centennial, Simcoe, Citra and Mosaic hops.
name: Crankshaft IPA

description: This copper colored American IPA took a wild left turn when we fermented it with our favorite Trappist ale yeast. Charged with hops, followed closely by a clove and pepper Belgian yeast character.
name: Crazy Ivan

description: The Cream Dream Series is our ongoing array of large, hop-centric American IPAs based on the malt profile of our cream ale. Our seventh edition balances orange peel bitterness with a cavalcade of citrus and tropical fruit hop flavors.
name: Cream Dream 007

description: A delicious blend of Galaxy and Mosaic hops greets you in both the bouqet and flavor of this beer. Crisp hop bitterness on the finish.
name: Creative Name IPA

description: This IPA is packed with American hops that are added at every stage of the brewing process. Big notes of citrus in the aroma are complimented by a smooth bitterness and crisp, piney finish. We added a F*** ton of hops to this beer in hopes that we please even the pickiest of hop heads.
name: Crescent Fresh

description:
A black IPA made with dark roasty grains and a
wallop of hops! Cretaceous has a generous
amount of Pacific Northwest Cascade, Mosaic,
Columbus, and Citra hops. This beer aint done
yet…we age the beer on barrel derived toasted
oak chips that still have a fresh bourbon taste.
Cheers to dark IPA and carnivorous beer
drinking dinosaurs!
name: Cretaceous Black IPA

description: The hop profile in this brew is led by notes of citrus, tangerine and tropical fruit with little pin in the background.  The malt backbone provides balance to every sip.
name: Crikey IPA

description: Inspired by West Coast I.P.A.'s, but brewed with Michigan style. The Crooked Tree is heavily dry hopped to give it a big aroma of pine and citrus. The flavors are big, yet very balanced between fresh hops and malt. Often described as "grapefruit" our hops give this beer an excellent fruit flavor that finishes dry, crisp, and clean. It will pour a nice deep copper color with a bit of haziness. Because of our almost patented "Intense Transfer Methods" our Crooked Tree has won several medals in the India Pale Ale category.
name: Crooked Tree I.P.A.

description: Crop Rotation is our ever changing IPA recipe that is aimed at showcasing the beloved hop plant. No two batches are quite the same, but the hops will always be front and center with a variety of great aromas and flavors.
name: Crop Rotation IPA

description: Award winning west coast style IPA. John Palmer, author of "How to brew" wrote in his BJCP competition sheet "It's hard to suggest improvement" about Urbana's west coast style, Cross Over IPA. Very aromatic with hints of tropical fruit and grape fruit with a very clean dry finish. Persistant big white head that seems to stays on top of your glass til you finish your pint.
name: Cross Over Ipa

description: Our flagship IPA is brewed in the West Coast style and inspired by the 1947 film noir of the same name starring the three Roberts (Mitchum, Ryan, and Young). Crossfire has a bold hop presence with notes of citrus and pine. Pale, Munich, and Crystal Malts provide a strong malt backbone, making this IPA extremely balanced and drinkable.
name: Crossfire IPA

description: Light Gold in color. Medium/full body, Notes of citrus and tropical fruit, slightly sweet carmel followed with piney bitter finish that lasts for days!
name: Crow Hop's Ipa

description: Don’t judge a book by its cover and don’t judge a beer by its color. If you pry Crowbar open, you’ll realize there’s more complexity to this beer than just its dark black hue. Crowbar is an IPA in disguise.…
name: Crowbar

description: Just shy of an Imperial IPA, this dry hopped beer is soon to become a favorite for American hop-heads.  Moderate malt character blends nicely with the combination of Chinook, Centennial and Cascade hops.
name: Crown Jewels IPA

description: Hailing from an Ashe County gem, Crumpler, and Weighing in at 8.5% and packing a Crippling punch of around 90 IBUs of all Citra hops, this Double IPA packs a wallop without totally knocking your head off. A very drinkable IPA with the trademark citrus aroma and flavor of the highly sought after Citra hops. Best enjoyed fresh
name: Crumpler Crippler Citra 2XIPA

description: In celebration of the spring and the start of baseball season we brewed an IPA that really knocks it out of the park! Bright Mandarina hops and a smooth malt body makes a super citrus, crushable IPA.
name: Crush City IPA

description: Crush IPA takes the citrus characteristics of Peak IPA and elevates them with a subtle addition of organic blood orange peel. The juicy citrus aroma really pops, and the brisk body of the beer is accented with notes of bright ripened fruit.
name: Crush IPA

description: We heart session beers. There's nothing quite like whiling away an afternoon with a six pack of something crisp, clean, and light enough to walk away from when the job is done. But we also demand flavor -- hops at that, and the more the better. Meet the Crusher: this poundable, single hop session IPA is brewed with 2-row barley and a touch of caramel malt for depth, accented with loads and loads of late-addition hops. The hops provide an IPA-sized dose of intensely fruity hop aroma without an overly bitter finish. We use a different hop every two months to showcase that variety of hop and its unique attributes. This is the IPA bar stools were invented for.
name: Crusher Single Hop Session IPA

description: Assertive American grown hops from the Yakima Valley in Washington are the cornerstone of this West Coast standard. Two-row pale malt and California Ale yeast combine with the citrusy-pine flavors and aromas of Centennial and Cascade hops. Balanced to accent a firm bitterness to allow the unique qualities of a Northern California-style IPA to shine.
name: Cryptic

description: A crisp and refreshing IPA exploding with fresh hop character, named for a somewhat forgotten yet amazing hop variety named Crystal. A unique hopping program gives this beer a massive, clean bitterness and fresh hop aroma bursting with hints of citrus and fresh fruit.
name: Crystal Hero

description: Myth has it that this style of beer originated during British colonial times as soldiers were shipped beer reserves in India. Hops were used as preservatives but that floral hop flavor and aroma that they instilled upon the beer were an unexpected benefit. However, this style didn't take off in America until the 'Craft Beer Revolution' took off in the 1980's on the American West Coast. Over the years, the IPA and its many off-shoots have become both an icon and a staple of American craft beer as they deviate from the watery and general flavorless product that has been popularized by 'Big Beer'.
name: CTZar

description: Collaboration with Evil Czech Brewing Co. IPA brewed with copious amounts of dank hops and cucumber.
name: Cuke Nukem

description: Our tenth Cult offering brings something new to the table with a nod to "Fight Club". The resinous and berry nose is followed by clean bitterness and a dry, smooth finish.
name: Cult 020: His Name Was Robert Paulson Ghost 271

description: Cumulus is a Northeast Style I.P.A. that is brewed with Oats and Wheats. The yeast strain gives it the hazy affected. This beer has a soft mouthfeel and is like drinking hop juice. Hopped with Citra, Simcoe, Amarillo, Centennial and Kohatu hops.
name: Cumulus

description: Mild beginning, hoppy in the middle and mellows out on the finish. A healthy dose of wheat adds complexity to this unfiltered hop-forward IPA/wheat hybrid. Medium bodied, bursting with flavor.
name: Cumulus Wheat IPA

description: CURIOSITY FOURTEEN - (American IPA 6.8% ABV) - Our burst of Curiosity persists… !  Brewed with a massive dose of Northwest American hops, Fourteen pours a brilliant hazy orange in the glass with a dense and creamy head.  We experience intense flavors and aromas of sweet orange, jackfruit, papaya, guava, and mango -  Perhaps the most purely tropical beer we’ve ever brewed…!  The finish is strong, providing balance to the sweet fruit flavor. Your patience will be awarded, as Fourteen’s complexity opens up as she warms...
name: Curiosity Fourteen

description: Bitter and balanced. A West Coast style IPA. Brilliant bouquet of grapefruit and tropical fruit on the nose, with hints of peach and lemon zest.
name: Curiosity IPA

description: Curious IPA is a powerfully hoppy India Pale Ale brewed using the finest pale ale malt and three complementary hops.  We're winemakers and so apply the classic practise used by Champagne, Cotes du Rhone and Claret who blend three grape varieties to create balance and depth. We use traditional English Golding; the fresh, sweet, delicate king of English hops, Bramling Cross; a forest fruity beauty, and Chinook; the punchy, spicy yet aromatic hop.
name: Curious IPA

description: An IPA based on the style of the pacific northwest. Intense hop aroma, citrusy hop flavour, dry finish
name: Curly Horse IPA

description: Each version features a different selection of hops. This batch contains Simcoe hops.
name: Curses Batch #1

description: Each version features a different selection of hops. This batch contains Falconers Flight hops.
name: Curses Batch #2

description: Each version features a different selection of hops. This batch contains Mosaic hops.
name: Curses Batch #3

description: Each version features a different selection of hops. This batch contains Mosaic, Chinook, and Falconers Flight hops.
name: Curses Batch #4

description: Each version features a different selection of hops. This batch contains Amarillo hops.
name: Curses Batch #5

description: Each version features a different selection of hops. This batch contains Green Bullet hops.
name: Curses Batch #6

description: Each version features a different selection of hops. This batch contains Experimental Hop #05256
name: Curses Batch #7

description: Each version features a different selection of hops. This batch contains Amarillo hops.
name: Curses Batch #8

description: Each version features a different selection of hops. This batch contains Pacific Jade hops.
name: Curses Batch #9

description: Newport Storm has always done things a little differently, but we like to think it’s for the better! Cyclone Will is no exception- this beer is as big and bold of a hopped-up beer as we’ve ever brewed! Following true West Coast IPA style, this latest in the Cyclone Series is nothing but pounds upon pounds of delicious hops! Named after the 4th founder of Newport Storm- Will Rafferty- who hails from the West Coast himself!
name: Cyclone Series Will

description: For the hop lover in all of us, we present Cyclops IPA. The substantial gravity is met by a cornucopia of 5 hop varieties, which yield striking flavor and aroma that results in one of the more balanced and aromatic IPA offerings you’ll wrap your hands around.
name: Cyclops IPA

description: A mix of West Coast IPA and English yeast along with four pounds of hops per barrel gives this heavenly IPA a larger- than- life citrusy hops flavor.   Six types of malt tame this wild brew and give it the hearty backbone this beer needs, bringing caramel, biscuit and bread flavors to your awaiting tongue.  And at 7.1% ABV, this is one beer that is to be reckoned with.  So kick back and enjoy this big, perfectly balanced IPA with flavors and aromas as rare and wild as a one-eyed Sasquatch.
name: Cysquatch IPA

description: Bold flavors of pear and banana balance rich notes of biscuit in this single hopped IPA. The light malt backbone and moderate body allow the unique character of the new Jarrylo hops to shine.
name: D'Town Drafts: Jarrylo IPA

description: Aromas of gooseberries, blueberries and red grapes precede just a hint of grassiness in this golden session IPA. Flavors of dark fruit and grass mirror the aromas, finishing with a lightly pleasant dryness.
name: D'Town Drafts: Moxee Session IPA

description: Sweet and spicy aromas and flavors of citrus and tropical fruit besiege your senses in our Rye IPA. The hoppy notes linger as they merge with earthy hints of rye.
name: D'Town Drafts: Rye IPA

description: Our IPA is a well hopped beer without too much bitterness. It has a great piney and citrus flavor due to Amarillo and Centennial hops used. Darker in color and a nice thick body, this beer is a great way to get introduced to IPA’s.
name: Da'Kine India Pale Ale

description: An easy drinking light bodied beer with a substantial tropical and citrus hop flavor and aroma. Contains cascade, crystal, citra, and columbus hops.
name: Daddy's Juice Session IPA

description: Our award winning flagship beer boasts five different hop varieties. Each hop variety contributes its own unique character that when blended combine to create pungent citrus and pine like hop flavors and aromas consistent of true northwest style IPA’s . Abundant hop aroma prepares the palate for the equally intense hop bite and flavor that lingers in this rich, deep brew.
name: Dagger Falls IPA

description: Don't let the name fool you. This beer is no mistake. A light copper colored ale with an intense hop nose and a distinct hop flavor with mild body and plenty of kick. For the true beer enthusiast this beer weighs in at 55 IBU's. A great beer with lots of flavor. Named after our friends at the Daily Crisis Dairy Farm here in Baltimore County, Maryland.
name: Daily Crisis IPA

description: Copper in color with a strong hop presence, which bounces around the mouth like a ferret happy to see its owner. The hop flavor and bitterness continue on through the finish while the malt presence supplies nice balance. A moderately strong medium bodied ale.
name: Dancing Ferret IPA

description: Our inaugural release boasts aromas of citrus, and dank, resinous pine. As the flavor opens, huge notes of stonefruit and dank resin give way to a juicy malt backbone and drying hop bitterness on the finish.
name: Dank & Sticky

description: IPA brewed with a 7 spice blend and Falconer’s Flight hops.
name: Dank You, Come Again!

description: With the colour of rich Porter but the punch of hops associated with IPA, our Black IPA is true deception in a glass. Three dry hop additions give this beer a scintillating aroma of pine and tropical fruit, while hints of toasted malt mix with big layers of US hop character from the addition of Simcoe and Mosaic varieties. What will you discover within the Dark Arches?
name: Dark Arches

description: It is a dark India Pale Ale (IPA) that combines a rich malty character with locally sourced hops from The Rhizome Republic of Freeville, NY.
name: Dark Devotion Black IPA

description: Expressive IPA released for Emerald City Comicon 2016. 2-row pale, honey and C-15 malts with oats and HBC 438, Mosaic and Chinook hops.
name: Dark Heron

description: This ale gets its strength and depth of character from the citrus/pine flavor of the hops. Moderately balanced with a medium body and malt character.
name: Dark Justice IPA

description: An dark American IPA with a generous dose of pacific northwest hops and some black malt for a nice roast malt flavor.
name: Dark Knight Black IPA

description: A special batch from our Pilot Program: A dark, malty IPA made with a special blend of rich crystal and roasted malts and hopped with such favorites as Centennial, Cascade, Apollo, and Amarillo.
name: Dark Racer

description: IPA - Black / Cascadian Dark Ale
name: Dark Shell

description: A black IPA brewed with 2 Row, Crystal Malt, and Midnight Wheat (a de-husked black malt), to give a dark appearance without the usual roastiness associated with dark malts.  Hopped aggressively with Citra, Simcoe, and Centennial hops.
name: Dark Side Black IPA

description: West Coast style IPA with an intense citrus hop flavor
name: Dart Dodger IPA

description: Dated * 1858 is named for the year Petaluma was incorporated and the use of California dates in the recipe. This Ruby IPA perfectly balances the earthy sweetness of medjool dates with the bitterness of Cascade hops for a taste that begins with a subtle, sweet aroma and flavor and finishes with a soft hopiness that doesn't linger for too long.
name: Dated * 1858

description: Here is a nice, smooth and hoppy offering from our pilot series. It’s quite a unique I.P.A. for the style. Using a similar but much larger grist bill as our EDS (Everday Special), its light and crisp malt profile tangos wonderfully with the additions of HBC-342, Chinook, Perle and Centennial hops. Pine, grapefruit and awesomeness is the first things that comes to mind while sipping on this easy drinking I.P.A. This one is for the Dawg Daze of our beautiful Flagstaff Winter. Enjoy friends.
name: Dawg Daze

description: DAX is local nickname for the Adirondacks and also the name for our family of IPA's. This is our version of the popular style using 5 varieties of hops in the boil and 2 varieties of dry hops. We don't skimp on malt either. We have carefully selected 5 different malts to balance out the hop character.
name: DAX - India Pale Ale

description: Awesome session IPA from South County Brewing Co.
name: Day Rider IPA

description: Spiced IPA. Toasted straw color, citrus and pine aroma, juniper ana resin flavors, firm bitter finish.
name: Daybreak IPA

description: Daydreamin' Session IPA is an ultra-crushable, crisp IPA
name: Daydreamin'

description: A juicy beat of hops - dripping with tropical, sunshiny Mosaic and sparkling with touches of Eldorado and Centennial.
name: DayGlow

description: This refreshing session IPA starts with a base Pilsner and Vienna Malt and then showcases the multiple additions of Warrior, Azacca and Citra hops, yielding tropical aromatics with hints of mango and grapefruit. Low in alcohol, BIG in flavor.
name: Daylight Savings IPA

description:
Jim Moorehouse, Nate Albrecht and Brad Zeller, three pals planning to open a Chicago brewpub under the moniker of Aleman, won first place at last year's Iron Brew homebrewing competition in the Windy City (judged by none other than Greg Koch, Jason Ebel of Two Brothers Brewing, and celebrated Chicago brewer, designer and author Randy Mosher). Their style-bending IPA artfully married the assertive tropical bite of Citra hops with amazing coffee flavor and aromatics to create something truly unique and exceptional.

Serendipitously, Two Brothers recently kicked off a new adventure roasting their own coffee beans, and provided just-in-time freshly roasted java for the brew. The result is an innovative IPA that's well balanced and intensely flavored thanks to the felicitous blend of hops and fresh roasted coffee.
name: Dayman Coffee IPA

description: A collaboration between Salish Sea Brewing Co. and American Brewing Co., both located on Dayton Street in Edmonds.  A smooth, light, and refreshing ale - Citra hops provide a fresh citrus aroma reminiscent of grapefruit.  A bit cloudy in appearance from the Kolsch yeast that stays in suspension in this unfiltered ale. Originally brewed for Hale's Bluegrass and Beer Festival in May 2014.
name: Dayton Street Session IPA

description: A fresh take on the hoppy session beer for the first warm and sunny days of the year. This is a very crisp straw colored ale with a fresh, zest ginger aroma with a subtle and smooth grapefruit and hop finish. Drinkable and delightful, very unique both in flavor and technique (we passed the beer through copious amounts of hops, fresh grapefruit peel, and fresh ginger on the way to being chilled.
name: Daywalker

description: DDH (Double Dry Hopped) Gen. Sherman is our classic West Coast Style IPA unfiltered and dry hopped a second time with additional Simcoe, Crystal, and Cascade hops. Dry hopping lends extra aroma and flavor to any beer. Double Dry Hopping this IPA gives it an even bigger floral citrus flavor and aroma that all hop heads love. Enjoy!
name: DDH (Double Dry Hopped) Gen. Sherman IPA
De Natte Gijt Hop met de Gijt

description: This is a smoked IPA.
name: De Natte Gijt Vredesgijt

description: Fort De Soto, the largest park within the Pinellas County Park System, consists of 1,136 acres made up of five interconnected islands. These keys are home to beach plants, mangroves, wetlands, palm hammocks, hardwoods and scores of native plants. The park is also home to more than 328 species of birds with new species being added every year. Between 1,000 A.D. and 1,500 A.D. Fort De Soto was inhabited by the Tocobaga Indians. On May 30, 1539 a well-known Spanish explorer, Hernando De Soto, landed on these shores. De Soto Low is a take on a new style that we dub, Micro IPA. Lower alcohol than both American IPAs and Session IPAs, our Micro IPA is only 2.3% ABV but is packed full of hop aroma, flavor, and bitterness. De Soto Low is brewed with generous amounts of Simcoe, Columbus, and Citra hops at 45 IBUs.
name: De Soto Low Micro IPA

description: Our best selling beer boasts a massive hop profile and rich English malts for a very balanced drinkable IPA.
name: De-Railed India Pale Ale

description:
A full bodied golden Pale Ale which pours with a linen white medium density head leaving spider web lace on the glass.

On the palate the flavour is sweet fruity malts up front (apricot, mango) with a bit of candy, and slight grassy notes which fall away to reveal a hint of biscuit with rather pleasant grapefruit and perfume undertones. 

This is a hop bomb, there is no doubt.  To the nose there is a mild malt aroma which accentuates the robust floral bouquet which is derived from the hops.

Medium full bodied ale with pleasant lingering hop finish.
name: Dead Elephant

description: Dead Horse IPA gives a deep bow to British IPA's. Made entirely from British Maris Otter barley malt, it has strong notes of butter and a deeper red color than most IPA's.
name: Dead Horse India Pale Ale

description: A classic American Style IPA dominated by citrus aroma and flavor, strong grapefruit notes and a sharp finish. An accidental recipe, resulting from the death of a kettle during the brewing process.
name: Dead Kettle

description: This extra hoppy ale is characteristic of the classic pale ales. Using the very flavorful Mount Hood, Liberty and Hallertau hops we have created classic IPA goodness every sailor knows.
name: Dead Man Walkin' IPA

description: First brewed for English troops that were stationed in India, IPAs have grown to become a modern day favorite. Its deep golden appearance is achieved with the finest premium base malts with a light touch of caramel malts for a bit of color. Our 2016 Death Breath Double IPA is well balanced for its ABV, dry-hopped for maximum American hop aromas and is followed by a huge fruity hop flavor.
name: Death Breath V2

description: This mega-hopped IPA has immense tropical fruit and citrus notes followed by an intense hop explosion on the finish.
name: Death by Dankness

description: We took the best of ADK'S Iroquois IPA and the best of OSB's IPA then added about double our normal amount of Citra, Centennial, Crystal and Cascade to the dry hop - then topped it all with whole bunch of Death Wish coffee beans
name: Death Wish Coffee IPA

description: IPA brewed with oats and wheat. Hopped generously with Columbus, Galaxy, and Simcoe. Gloomy and delicious!
name: Deathtripper

description: Our special 10th anniversary beer is the biggest IPA we have had the nerve to make. Almost all Pale malt, with less than one percent each of Carastan and Wheat makes a beer quite pale for its size at 19 plato OG. We added Chinook, Centennial and Cascade hops just about every place and every way we could think of - giving it lots of hop flavor and aroma and enough bitterness to complement the telltale sweetness of the malt. One patron says "It makes you smile so your mouth's big enough for the beer". 6.25% alcohol by weight 7.8% by volume.
name: Decade India Pale Ale

description: ‘Tis the season to celebrate, as we wrap up 2014 with the gift of a double IPA. Caramel and midnight wheat malts lend a festive reddish hue, while a Santa-sized triple dry-hop with Chinook and Simcoe™ delivers flavor and aroma by the sleighful. A dose of holiday cheer that belongs under your tree – whether you’ve been naughty or nice.
name: December IPA of the Month

description: Black Rye IPA
name: Deception

description: A perfect copper-colored American India Pale Ale abundant with juicy fruit-filled hop aromas. Malt sweetness takes a back seat to a medley of lush hop flavors, ranging from dank wet earthiness to bitter herbs and greens. The finish is punctuated by a clean and dry grassy bitterness.
name: DeclarationALE

description:
Our Year 'round ode to the Pacific Northwest hop

At DEBC, we like hops, but we like American hops most of all. Here we use some of our absolute favorites. However, they might not be used like you may expect, by using varieties with high alpha acid contents (which means more potential for bitterness) and using them in ways that emphasize the flavor and aroma we can render a rather bitter ale with over the top tropical fruit, citrus, pine, floral and more hop derived aroma and flavor.
name: Deep Ellum IPA

description: American IPA
name: Deep Woods Delusion

description:
A hop driven IPA with a malty finish.
Del Norte Titan is ranked as the world's fourth largest coast redwood and is located in Jedediah Smith State Park.
name: Del Norte IPA

description: Dulachan is an in-your-face/front-and-center/West-Coast-style American IPA. Brewed with Pale, CaraVienna and Biscuit malts and hopped (and dry hopped) to 70 IBU’s with Simcoe, Citra, Amarillo & Columbus. At only 5.6%ABV, this beer packs a huge hop flavor and aroma without a lot of bite from the bitterness and alcohol. Named after the Irish ’Grim Reaper’, this beer will impress and astound!
name: Delachan IPA

description: Bottle description: Great beer is for everyone and anyone with the good taste to recognize it, not just a niche group like us über beer geeks. So, when we developed this pleasantly bitter, deliciously citrusy, hop-driven IPA, we took it as an opportunity to go a step further and do something we’d spent over a year researching and perfecting: creating a beer that makes it possible for nearly everyone to experience our aggressive, no-holds-barred approach to craft brewing. It’s a flavorful, cutting-edge, modern-day IPA for everyone. Lemondrop and El Dorado hops provide plenty of fruity citrus character and a burst of hop zing that sings on the palate. We’re proud to present it to those who already know us for our IPA prowess and to those who, so far, have only heard the legends.
name: Delicious IPA

description: Delta 9 IPA is brewed in the traditional northwest fashion with a rich blend of malts and 6 different hop varieties.
name: Delta 9 IPA

description: 14th in this second series of American IPAs.  Rich golden in colour with creamy and nutty malt on the aroma and light citrus fruit.  The finish is long and bitter with a strong hop finish.
name: Delta IPA

description: Ahtanum, Mosaic, Simcoe, and Chinook hops bring stone fruit, citrus and pine flavors and aromas to a solid malt backbone.
name: Delta One Bravo IPA

description: Demo is a deliciously dark lick of an India Pale Ale. It’s medley of roasted malts and heady hops will have your senses dancing to the beat of a different I.P.A.
name: Demo
